Commentary Text: Unadkat to Rahul, no run, a brilliant last over by Unadkat as he concedes only 4 runs. Commentary Text: Murugan Ashwin to Manish Pandey, out Bowled!! The leg-stump is uprooted, and Murugan Ashwin strikes in his final over. Much needed for Mumbai Indians because the two Karnataka boys were simply toying with the bowlers. A tossed up delivery by Murugan Ashwin, this dips a touch and Manish swings across the line to get beaten. This didn't spin much, kept straight and rattled timber. The leg spinner looks relieved as the partnership has been broken. The foundation has been laid though, time for the big hitters to come in and have a go at the opposition bowlers. Manish Pandey b Murugan Ashwin 38(29) [4s-6]

Commentary Text: Fabian Allen to de Kock, out Lbw!! QDK has a word with his partner and decides to walk off. Looked very adjacent. Tried the reverse sweep and missed it completely, struck plumb in front of middle and off and it would have crashed into one of those. Fabian Allen isn't a huge turner and usually bowls stump-to-stump, so the reverse sweep is a slightly risky option considering the pace he bowls. de Kock lbw b Fabian Allen 24(13) [4s-4 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to Rohit, out Caught by de Kock!! Edged and taken! Early wicket for Lucknow as Avesh gets the MI skipper. A short of a length delivery outside off, and Rohit looks to slice this through the off-side. He is a touch low in doing so and gets a feather to de Kock.
